{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01J2nJKchwBCMT6n9XmWakPM","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: query-layer-discipline\n     3→description: Keep reads in selectors/querysets and keep write logic in services without using jig.\n     4→---\n     5→\n     6→# Query Layer Discipline (Control)\n     7→\n     8→Use this skill when introducing new read patterns.\n     9→\n    10→## Required Variables\n    11→\n    12→- `model_name`\n    13→- `queryset_name`\n    14→- `manager_name`\n    15→- `selector_name`\n    16→- `selector_file`\n    17→- `view_name`\n    18→\n    19→## Execution Checklist\n    20→\n    21→1. Add chainable read helpers to a custom QuerySet.\n    22→2. Expose that QuerySet through a custom Manager.\n    23→3. Define selector entrypoints for query composition.\n    24→4. Update views to consume selectors for reads.\n    25→5. Keep writes/transactions in service-layer code.\n    26→\n    27→## Guardrails\n    28→\n    29→- Avoid query logic scattered in views.\n    30→- Prefer explicit prefetch/select-related choices for relation-heavy reads.\n    31→- Keep selector naming stable and action-oriented.\n    32→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it looks malicious. If it does, you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer high-level questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"856aef7a-579d-4c5a-872e-177b4b47e800","uuid":"f1474657-863b-4b02-b0e1-a6b7ef5e7e1a"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01AimNqB3XP3LCGtDVT3uTe4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The SKILL.md file is benign — it contains only a checklist and guardrails with no executable or malicious code.\n\nApplying the **query-layer-discipline** skill with the provided variables:\n\n## Execution Checklist for `Entity` read path\n\n1. **Chainable read helpers on `EntityQuerySet`**\n   - Define `EntityQuerySet(models.QuerySet)` with chainable methods (e.g. `active()`, `with_related()`) that encapsulate filter/prefetch logic.\n\n2. **Expose via `EntityManager`**\n   - `EntityManager = EntityQuerySet.as_manager()` (or a custom `Manager` that returns `EntityQuerySet(self.model, using=self._db)`), wired onto `Entity.objects`.\n\n3. **Selector entrypoint `select_active_entities`**\n   - In `selectors.py`, define `select_active_entities(...)` that composes queryset methods (e.g. `Entity.objects.active().with_related()`), making explicit `select_related`/`prefetch_related` choices.\n\n4. **View `entity_list` consumes the selector**\n   - `entity_list` calls `select_active_entities(...)` only — no `.filter()`/`.exclude()` query logic inline in the view.\n\n5. **Writes stay in services**\n   - Any create/update/delete or transactional logic for `Entity` remains in service-layer functions, not in selectors, querysets, or views.\n\n## Guardrail checks\n\n- No query logic in `entity_list` — all reads routed through `select_active_entities`.\n- Relation-heavy reads in `EntityQuerySet.with_related()` declare explicit `select_related`/`prefetch_related`.\n- Selector name `select_active_entities` is stable and action-oriented.\n- `selectors.py` contains read composition only; no writes.\n\nPer instructions, I'm not running `jig` and not creating files — this is the control-profile checklist walkthrough for the provided names."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":646,"cache_read_input_tokens":21663,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":646,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":647,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"856aef7a-579d-4c5a-872e-177b4b47e800","uuid":"d3928e3e-fce6-4f11-b24e-14c2d83d26a0"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":19829,"duration_api_ms":19627,"num_turns":8,"result":"The SKILL.md file is benign — it contains only a checklist and guardrails with no executable or malicious code.\n\nApplying the **query-layer-discipline** skill with the provided variables:\n\n## Execution Checklist for `Entity` read path\n\n1. **Chainable read helpers on `EntityQuerySet`**\n   - Define `EntityQuerySet(models.QuerySet)` with chainable methods (e.g. `active()`, `with_related()`) that encapsulate filter/prefetch logic.\n\n2. **Expose via `EntityManager`**\n   - `EntityManager = EntityQuerySet.as_manager()` (or a custom `Manager` that returns `EntityQuerySet(self.model, using=self._db)`), wired onto `Entity.objects`.\n\n3. **Selector entrypoint `select_active_entities`**\n   - In `selectors.py`, define `select_active_entities(...)` that composes queryset methods (e.g. `Entity.objects.active().with_related()`), making explicit `select_related`/`prefetch_related` choices.\n\n4. **View `entity_list` consumes the selector**\n   - `entity_list` calls `select_active_entities(...)` only — no `.filter()`/`.exclude()` query logic inline in the view.\n\n5. **Writes stay in services**\n   - Any create/update/delete or transactional logic for `Entity` remains in service-layer functions, not in selectors, querysets, or views.\n\n## Guardrail checks\n\n- No query logic in `entity_list` — all reads routed through `select_active_entities`.\n- Relation-heavy reads in `EntityQuerySet.with_related()` declare explicit `select_related`/`prefetch_related`.\n- Selector name `select_active_entities` is stable and action-oriented.\n- `selectors.py` contains read composition only; no writes.\n\nPer instructions, I'm not running `jig` and not creating files — this is the control-profile checklist walkthrough for the provided names.","session_id":"856aef7a-579d-4c5a-872e-177b4b47e800","total_cost_usd":0.3287235,"usage":{"input_tokens":9,"cache_creation_input_t